{"cursor":"7481","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nA 'gene gun' or a 'biolistic particle delivery system', originally designed for\nplant transformation, is a device for injecting cells with genetic information.\nThe payload is an elemental particle of a heavy metal coated with plasmid DNA.\nThis technique is often simply referred to as 'bioballistics' or 'biolistics'.\n\nThis device is able to transform almost any type of cell, including plants, and\nis not limited to genetic material of the nucleus: it can also transform\norganelles, including plastids.\n","linknr":249,"url":"Biolistics","recorded":1362480576,"links":24,"instances":["cell_biology","genetics"],"pdf":["http://www.ecommons.cornell.edu/bitstream/1813/25239/1/018_33.pdf"],"categories":["Molecular biology","Molecular genetics","Laboratory techniques","Gene delivery"],"headings":["Design","Application","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Genegun.jpg/220px-Genegun.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["transformation","genetics"],["callus","cell_biology"],["transformation","genetics"],["transformation","genetics"]],"members":["callus","transformation"],"related":["Plant","Transformation_(genetics)","Genetics","Chemical_element","Heavy_metals","Plasmid","DNA","Plastids","Air_gun","Tungsten","John_C_Sanford","Reporter_gene","Nail_gun","Polyethylene","Helium","Gold","Silver","Callus_(cell_biology)","Petri_dish","Chromosome","Northern_blot","Auxins","Gibberellins","Totipotency","Ti_plasmid","Transformation_(genetics)","DNA_vaccination","Alzheimer's_Disease","Transformation_(genetics)","Microinjection"]}